    <a title="Carole" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7630646-carole"><img alt="Carole" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1530841494p2/7630646.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2651165697?book_show_action=true">Jun 23, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Carole" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Carole" href="/user/show/7630646-carole">Carole</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7630646-carole?shelf=read-2019">read-2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7630646-carole?shelf=coming-of-age">coming-of-age</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2651165697" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4566422748266581540">4.5 Eldonna Edwards is one of my favorite authors, creating realistic, interesting characters. I was quickly drawn in to the life of Clover Blue and his family at Saffron Community. The setting is the 1970s and Clover witnesses one of his sister mother&apos;s giving birth. This makes him think about who his &quot;real&quot; parents might be. He came into this loving hippie family as a toddler, and now questions how he got there. I could easily picture the characters of Doobie, Jade, Willow, Wave, Goji and his </span>
  <span id="freeText4566422748266581540" style="display:none">4.5 Eldonna Edwards is one of my favorite authors, creating realistic, interesting characters. I was quickly drawn in to the life of Clover Blue and his family at Saffron Community. The setting is the 1970s and Clover witnesses one of his sister mother's giving birth. This makes him think about who his "real" parents might be. He came into this loving hippie family as a toddler, and now questions how he got there. I could easily picture the characters of Doobie, Jade, Willow, Wave, Goji and his best friend, Harmony. It is a wonderful coming of age story with a new taste for me. I have never read anything quite like this, and I am already looking forward to this author's next book!</span>
