              <span id="reviewTextContainer2602308361" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17530942013274639267">&quot;Everything happens for a Reason.&quot; <br/>I was quickly engaged in this novel where the setting takes place in a commune during the 70&apos;s.<br/>The peace of the characters made me take my time reading each page.<br/> I immediately felt a serenity and became a part of the this group living and loving in nature. <br/>The main character Clover Blue, is a ten year old with many questions for his &quot;family&quot;. How did he get to this fabulous residence? Who are really his parents? Does he have other family members?<br/>Will he find t</span>
  <span id="freeText17530942013274639267" style="display:none">"Everything happens for a Reason." <br />I was quickly engaged in this novel where the setting takes place in a commune during the 70's.<br />The peace of the characters made me take my time reading each page.<br /> I immediately felt a serenity and became a part of the this group living and loving in nature. <br />The main character Clover Blue, is a ten year old with many questions for his "family". How did he get to this fabulous residence? Who are really his parents? Does he have other family members?<br />Will he find the answers he seeks as the time goes on? <br />Eldonna Edwards has once more written a beautiful tale of love, family, friendship and hope that I truly believe everyone will enjoy.</span>
